may have been rare, but that roads were there supporting traffic
by wagon and cart, as well as horseback. There were evidently
Roman roads still in use. That the need for roads was recognized
is demonstrated by the public responsibility to maintain roads by
doing assigned regular repairs; and there is documented evidence
that &quot;In 1611 he (Shakespeare) was one of a number of citizens
