MENENIUS

For corn at their own rates; whereof, they say,
The city is well stored.
(unquote)

In characterizing Shakespeare as a crusty businessman, Diana
Price reports that, &quot;Many of Shakespeare's business records
involve mercenary activities. In 1598, Shakespeare was hoarding
commercial quantities of grain during a famine.&quot;

So, not only was the importance of roads recognized by the state,
but Shakespeare participated in their maintenance; and a
particular motive for attending to roads between marketing
centers was an economy favoring transportation and hording of
produce for greater profit, in which Shakespeare was possibly
participating despite awareness of it as a form of usury.

