of a close ally (France) in the long, bitter
expensive war with Spain -- showing him
in all manner of ridiculous postures.

It would have been rather like seeing a play
on Broadway in, say, 1944 which made fun
of Churchill. Or better -- given that the State
was authoritarian, and had full control over
the stage -- rather like seeing a play in
Moscow in 1943 which caricatured Roosevelt
on the public stage.

