American Federation of Television and Radio Artists -- radio and live
and taped television (the exact demarcation has been a bit fuzzy of
late, due to the introduction of film-quality digital video).
American Guild of Variety Artists -- originally vaudeville, now chiefly
concerned with Las Vegas and Disney World, etc..
American Guild of Musical Artists -- opera (singers only).

Furthermore, nearly all theatre activity is concentrated in New York,
while nearly all film and television is concentrated in Los Angeles.
